        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-20 07:27:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nUnder config directory it is ok not to parametrize. the sed in config-init.sh will take care of this:\nSED_NS_STRINGS=(\n  \"s/\\.onap-/\\.${NAMESPACE}-/g\"\n...\nThere are many other occurrences of onap- in config. example: appc/conf/appc.properties",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "d386564faafcc22ebfa2a21019da16d98e096c72",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 137,
          "name": "Alexis de Talhouet",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "adetalhouet89@gmail.com",
          "username": "adetalhouet"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-20 12:24:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> SED_NS_STRINGS=(\"s/\\.onap-/\\.${NAMESPACE}-/g\"\n\nThis is going to be _way_ to dangerous. We cannot assume that \".onap-\" is only used for namespace. It can be used in any other occurence without us knowing (I think).\nThe solution is to parametrized this completely. Hence where the namespace is expected, we can put something like DEPLOYMENT_NAMESPACE_HERE and then sed on this.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "008dcdb27a7639328e4bb619ade01a40189bf1bb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 497,
          "name": "Borislav Glozman",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "borislav.glozman@amdocs.com",
          "username": "BorislavG"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-20 12:26:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > SED_NS_STRINGS=(\"s/\\.onap-/\\.${NAMESPACE}-/g\"\n > \n > This is going to be _way_ to dangerous. We cannot assume that\n > \".onap-\" is only used for namespace. It can be used in any other\n > occurence without us knowing (I think).\n > The solution is to parametrized this completely. Hence where the\n > namespace is expected, we can put something like DEPLOYMENT_NAMESPACE_HERE\n > and then sed on this.\n\nI agree with you. However let's do it in a concentrated manner everywhere in configuration once and not in small parts. Otherwise it will be confusing and we will forget some places.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
